name: saturated-thickness-of-the-high-plains-aquifer-colorado-2000
notes: These data are in support of report DS 472 (Arnold and others, 2009). This data set represents the saturated thickness of the High Plains aquifer within Colorado. The water levels used in generating the water-table data were collected from High Plains wells in the year 2000. Saturated thickness was derived by subtracting aquifer-base elevation from water-table elevation.
